{
  "id": "rj",
  "name": "RJ",
  "color": "#e8e4d8",
  "stage": "last-resort",
  "lore": {
    "tagline": "The Gatekeeper. The ghosts are art. The BB gun isn't.",
    "personality": "Bombay Beach's resident ghost artist and the Biennale's first line of defense — a weathered, unhurried desert artist in a straw hat who fosters stray birds, rides his mini-excavator around town like a horse, and settles most disputes with a lever-action BB gun and infinite patience. Tao calls him the Gatekeeper; RJ calls it keeping the lot tidy.",
    "backstory": "RJ came to Bombay Beach for the quiet and stayed for the ghosts — the ones he builds. His white sheet-ghost installations haunt fences and rooftops all over town, crowned by the World's Tallest Ghost towering over the Ghost Theater. He fosters every bird the desert dumps on him, digs art cars out of the mud with his excavator, and when the Biennale needs a door watched, the Patron Prince asks RJ. Challengers who want Tao answer to the BB gun first."
  },
  "winQuotes": [
    "Another ghost for the collection.",
    "The Prince said no visitors.",
    "The birds saw the whole thing.",
    "Get off my lot."
  ],
  "vo": {
    "kiai": [
      "Pow!",
      "Git!",
      "Hah!",
      "Boo!",
      "Plink!",
      "Yaw!"
    ],
    "hurt": [
      "Agh!",
      "Dang it!",
      "Ow!",
      "Hey now!",
      "Grr!",
      "Tsk!"
    ],
    "victory": [
      "Another ghost for the collection.",
      "The birds saw everything.",
      "Get off my lot.",
      "Ooo-ooo yourself."
    ]
  },
  "arcade": {
    "motivation": "RJ doesn't care who wins the Biennale — he cares who tramples his lot getting there. Tao pays him in diesel and birdseed to watch the gate, and RJ watches it like the desert watches everything: patiently, with a BB gun across his knees. If you want the Patron Prince, you go through the Gatekeeper.",
    "ending": "With Tao dethroned, RJ shrugs and gets back to work. There's a new ghost to raise — the tallest yet, stitched from a champion's banner — and the birds need feeding, and somebody left an art car axle-deep in the mud again. Bombay Beach doesn't need a champion. It needs a caretaker. It's always had one."
  },
